00:16:28,290 --> 00:16:32,712
"To Washington Bartholomew Hogwallop,

243
00:16:32,962 --> 00:16:34,380
from his lovin' Cora."

244
00:16:34,714 --> 00:16:40,052
- "Amor fidel... is."
- It was in his bureau,

245
00:16:40,386 --> 00:16:43,556
I reckon it'll fetch us enough
for a good auto voiture

246
00:16:43,806 --> 00:16:45,558
and a little leftover besides.

247
00:16:45,891 --> 00:16:48,311
Whoo! You got light fingers, Everett.

248
00:16:48,561 --> 00:16:52,231
- Gopher?
- You miserable little snake.

249
00:16:52,565 --> 00:16:54,317
You stole from my kin!

250
00:16:54,567 --> 00:16:57,069
Who was fixin' to betray us.

251
00:16:57,320 --> 00:16:59,322
You didn't know that at the time.

252
00:16:59,572 --> 00:17:01,657
So I borrowed it till I did know.

253
00:17:01,824 --> 00:17:03,826
That don't make no sense!

254
00:17:03,993 --> 00:17:06,829
A fool seeks logic
in the chambers of the heart.

255
00:17:07,163 --> 00:17:11,667
What the hell is that singing?

256
00:17:13,085 --> 00:17:18,758
Appears to be some kind
of a... congregation.

257
00:17:18,924 --> 00:17:22,595
Care for some gopher?

258
00:17:24,430 --> 00:17:26,265
No, thank you, Delmar.

259
00:17:26,432 --> 00:17:29,352
A third of a gopher'd
only arouse my appetite

260
00:17:29,685 --> 00:17:31,937
without beddin' her back down.

261
00:17:32,188 --> 00:17:34,440
Oh, you can have the whole thing.

262
00:17:34,774 --> 00:17:37,610
Me and Pete already had one.

263
00:17:37,943 --> 00:17:44,950
We ran across
a whole... gopher... village.

264
00:17:49,622 --> 00:17:53,042
<i>O brothers, let's go down</i>

265
00:17:53,376 --> 00:17:56,963
<i>Let's go down, come on down</i>

266
00:17:57,338 --> 00:18:00,633
<i>Come on, brothers, let's go down</i>

267
00:18:00,967 --> 00:18:05,012
<i>Down in the river to pray</i>

268
00:18:05,304 --> 00:18:09,058
<i>As I went down in the river to pray</i>

269
00:18:09,308 --> 00:18:12,186
<i>Studyin' about that good old way</i>

270
00:18:12,561 --> 00:18:15,898
<i>And who shall wear the starry crown</i>

271
00:18:16,107 --> 00:18:20,486
<i>Good Lord, show me the way</i>

272
00:18:20,653 --> 00:18:24,240
<i>O fathers, let's go down</i>

273
00:18:24,490 --> 00:18:28,077
<i>Let's go down, come on down</i>

274
00:18:28,244 --> 00:18:31,622
<i>O fathers, let's go down</i>

275
00:18:31,914 --> 00:18:36,085
<i>Down in the river to pray</i>

276
00:18:36,419 --> 00:18:40,256
<i>As I went down in the river to pray</i>

277
00:18:40,464 --> 00:18:43,592
<i>Studying about that good old way</i>

278
00:18:43,843 --> 00:18:47,179
<i>And who shall wear the robe and crown</i>

279
00:18:47,388 --> 00:18:52,018
<i>Good lord, show me the way</i>

280
00:18:52,351 --> 00:18:55,730
<i>O mothers, let's go down</i>

281
00:18:55,938 --> 00:18:59,233
<i>Come on down, don't you wanna go down?</i>

282
00:18:59,442 --> 00:19:03,195
<i>Come on, mothers, let's go down...</i>

283
00:19:03,404 --> 00:19:06,532
Well, I guess hard times flush the chumps.

284
00:19:06,782 --> 00:19:08,868
Everybody's lookin' for answers.

285
00:19:12,788 --> 00:19:14,498
Where the hell's he going?

286
00:19:14,749 --> 00:19:18,669
The Father, the Son and the Holy Ghost.

287
00:19:18,919 --> 00:19:22,840
<i>Good Lord, show me the way</i>

288
00:19:23,049 --> 00:19:27,470
<i>O sinners, let's go down...</i>

289
00:19:27,803 --> 00:19:30,139
Well, I'll be a son of a bitch.

290
00:19:30,306 --> 00:19:32,308
Delmar's been saved.

291
00:19:32,600 --> 00:19:35,561
Well, that's it, boys.
I been redeemed.

292
00:19:35,728 --> 00:19:39,982
The preacher done washed away
all my sins and transgressions.

293
00:19:40,232 --> 00:19:43,027
It's the straight and narrow
from here on out.

294
00:19:43,319 --> 00:19:45,821
And heaven everlasting's my reward.

295
00:19:46,030 --> 00:19:49,283
Delmar, what are you on about?
We got bigger fish to fry.

296
00:19:49,492 --> 00:19:52,495
The preacher said
all my sins is washed away,

297
00:19:52,745 --> 00:19:55,748
including that Piggly Wiggly
I knocked over in Yazoo.

298
00:19:55,998 --> 00:19:58,084
You said you was innocent of that.

299
00:19:58,292 --> 00:20:00,586
Well, I was lyin'.

300
00:20:00,753 --> 00:20:04,548
And the preacher said that
that sin's been washed away, too.

301
00:20:04,757 --> 00:20:08,052
Neither God nor man's
got nothin' on me now.

302
00:20:08,344 --> 00:20:13,265
Come on in, boys.
The water is fine.

303
00:20:19,188 --> 00:20:22,024
Come on, boy.
There, boy. Good doggy.

304
00:20:24,527 --> 00:20:28,406
All right, boys, we got the scent.

305
00:20:30,992 --> 00:20:34,787
- The preacher said it absolved us.
- For Him, not for the law.

306
00:20:34,954 --> 00:20:37,707
I gave you credit for
more brains than Delmar.

307
00:20:37,915 --> 00:20:41,961
- But witnesses seen us redeemed.
- That's not the issue, Delmar.

308
00:20:42,295 --> 00:20:45,464
Even square with the Lord,
Mississippi's hard-nosed.

309
00:20:45,715 --> 00:20:49,135
You shoulda joined us, Everett.
It couldn'a hurt none.

310
00:20:49,385 --> 00:20:52,763
Hell, it woulda washed away
the stink of that pomade.

311
00:20:53,139 --> 00:20:56,684
Joining you fools in superstition?
Thank you, anyway.

312
00:20:56,934 --> 00:21:02,273
And I like the smell of my hair,
the pleasin' odour's half the point.

313
00:21:02,481 --> 00:21:04,483
Baptism!

314
00:21:04,650 --> 00:21:06,986
You two are dumber than a bag of hammers.

315
00:21:07,320 --> 00:21:09,196
You're my cross to bear.

316
00:21:09,405 --> 00:21:14,285
Pull over, Everett. Let's give
that coloured boy a lift.

317
00:21:20,249 --> 00:21:22,627
You folks going past Tishomingo?

318
00:21:22,835 --> 00:21:25,755
Sure, hop in.

319
00:21:32,762 --> 00:21:35,014
How you doin', son? Name's Everett.

320
00:21:35,348 --> 00:21:38,643
These two soggy sons of bitches
are Pete and Delmar.

321
00:21:39,018 --> 00:21:42,772
Keep your fingers away from Pete's
mouth, he ain't eaten for 13 years,

322
00:21:42,938 --> 00:21:45,274
'cept prison food and greasy horse.

323
00:21:45,566 --> 00:21:49,445
Thanks for the lift, sir.
My name's Tommy. Tommy Johnson.

324
00:21:49,737 --> 00:21:51,614
How you doin', Tommy?

325
00:21:51,822 --> 00:21:54,867
Say, I haven't seen a house
out here for miles.

326
00:21:55,117 --> 00:21:57,620
Why are you out in the middle of nowhere?

327
00:21:57,870 --> 00:22:00,539
I had to be at that crossroads
last midnight.

328
00:22:00,873 --> 00:22:02,750
Sell my soul to the devil.

329
00:22:02,959 --> 00:22:05,503
Ain't it a small world,
spiritually speakin'?

330
00:22:05,711 --> 00:22:09,882
Pete and Delmar just been saved.
I'm the only one still unaffiliated.

331
00:22:10,132 --> 00:22:12,218
It's no laughin' matter.

332
00:22:12,551 --> 00:22:14,303
What'd the devil give you for it?

333
00:22:14,553 --> 00:22:18,015
Well, he taught me to play
this here guitar real good.

334
00:22:18,224 --> 00:22:22,436
Oh, son, for that you traded
your everlasting soul?

335
00:22:22,812 --> 00:22:24,271
Well, I wasn't usin' it.

336
00:22:24,480 --> 00:22:28,651
I've always wondered,
what's the devil look like?

337
00:22:28,818 --> 00:22:32,405
Well, there are all manner
of lesser imps and demons,

338
00:22:32,613 --> 00:22:36,242
but Satan hisself is red and scaly
with a bifurcated tail,

339
00:22:36,575 --> 00:22:39,996
- and he carries a hayfork.
- Oh, no. No, sir.

340
00:22:40,162 --> 00:22:43,666
He's white.
As white as you folks.

341
00:22:43,833 --> 00:22:46,752
With empty eyes and a big, hollow voice.

342
00:22:47,003 --> 00:22:50,756
He travelled around
with a mean old hound, that's right.

343
00:22:50,923 --> 00:22:52,925
He told you to go to Tishomingo?

344
00:22:53,092 --> 00:22:55,928
Well, no, sir.
Why, that was my idea.

345
00:22:56,262 --> 00:22:58,014
I heard there's a man there,

346
00:22:58,347 --> 00:23:00,599
pays folks money to sing into his can.

347
00:23:00,933 --> 00:23:04,770
They say he pays extra
if'n you play real good.

348
00:23:05,021 --> 00:23:06,856
Tishomingo, huh?

349
00:23:07,106 --> 00:23:08,691
How much he pay?

350
00:23:25,124 --> 00:23:29,795
All right, boys, follow my lead.

351
00:23:33,883 --> 00:23:36,302
Hello?

352
00:23:36,636 --> 00:23:41,223
- Who's the honcho here?
- I am. Who are you?

353
00:23:41,390 --> 00:23:45,895
Well, sir, I'm Jordan Rivers,
and these are the Soggy Bottom Boys,

354
00:23:46,062 --> 00:23:48,064
out of Cottonillia, Mississippi.

355
00:23:48,314 --> 00:23:50,650
Songs of salvation to salve the soul.

356
00:23:50,983 --> 00:23:54,737
Uh, we hear that you pay good money
to sing into a can.

357
00:23:54,987 --> 00:23:58,324
Well, that all depends.
You boys do Negro songs?

358
00:23:58,491 --> 00:24:03,412
Um... Well, uh, sir, we are Negroes.

359
00:24:03,579 --> 00:24:07,667
All except for our accomp... accomp...
the fella that plays the guitar.

360
00:24:07,917 --> 00:24:10,086
Yeah, well, I don't record Negro songs.

361
00:24:10,419 --> 00:24:13,756
No, I'm lookin' for
some old-timey material.

362
00:24:14,006 --> 00:24:16,008
People can't seem to get enough

363
00:24:16,258 --> 00:24:19,679
since we started broadcasting it
on the Pappy O'Daniel Flour Hour,

364
00:24:20,012 --> 00:24:22,181
so thank you for stopping by, but...

365
00:24:22,515 --> 00:24:27,269
Sir, the Soggy Bottom Boys have been
steeped in old-timey material.

366
00:24:27,520 --> 00:24:30,189
- Heck, we're silly with it.
- That's right.

367
00:24:30,523 --> 00:24:32,525
Right. We ain't really Negroes.

368
00:24:32,775 --> 00:24:34,860
All except for our accompanist.

369
00:24:37,530 --> 00:24:41,784
<i>I am a man</i>

370
00:24:41,951 --> 00:24:44,787
<i>Of constant sorrow</i>

371
00:24:45,037 --> 00:24:51,043
<i>I've seen trouble all my days</i>

372
00:24:51,294 --> 00:24:55,631
<i>I bid farewell</i>

373
00:24:55,965 --> 00:24:58,467
<i>To old Kentucky</i>

374
00:24:58,801 --> 00:25:01,053
<i>The place where I</i>

375
00:25:01,304 --> 00:25:03,973
<i>Was born and raised</i>

376
00:25:04,223 --> 00:25:06,976
<i>The place where he</i>

377
00:25:07,310 --> 00:25:10,646
<i>Was born and raised</i>

378
00:25:10,896 --> 00:25:15,234
<i>For six long years</i>

379
00:25:15,568 --> 00:25:18,070
<i>I've been in trouble</i>

380
00:25:18,404 --> 00:25:20,990
<i>No pleasure here</i>

381
00:25:21,324 --> 00:25:24,660
<i>On Earth I found</i>

382
00:25:24,827 --> 00:25:29,081
<i>For in this world</i>

383
00:25:29,332 --> 00:25:31,500
<i>I'm bound to ramble</i>

384
00:25:31,751 --> 00:25:34,754
<i>I have no friends</i>

385
00:25:34,920 --> 00:25:37,590
<i>To help me now</i>

386
00:25:37,840 --> 00:25:40,343
<i>He has no friends</i>

387
00:25:40,676 --> 00:25:44,096
<i>To help him now</i>

388
00:25:44,430 --> 00:25:48,851
<i>Maybe your friends think</i>

389
00:25:49,101 --> 00:25:51,604
<i>I'm just a stranger</i>

390
00:25:51,937 --> 00:25:54,357
<i>My face you never</i>

391
00:25:54,690 --> 00:25:55,941
<i>Will see no more</i>

392
00:25:58,444 --> 00:26:03,199
<i>But there is one promise</i>

393
00:26:03,532 --> 00:26:05,534
<i>That is given</i>

394
00:26:05,701 --> 00:26:08,287
<i>I'll meet you on</i>

395
00:26:08,621 --> 00:26:11,123
<i>God's golden shore</i>

396
00:26:11,457 --> 00:26:14,043
<i>He'll meet you on</i>

397
00:26:14,293 --> 00:26:19,298
<i>God's golden shore</i>

398
00:26:20,633 --> 00:26:24,136
Whoo! Hot damn, son!
You did sell your soul to the devil!

399
00:26:25,972 --> 00:26:29,809
Boy, that was some mighty fine
a-pickin' and a-singin'.

400
00:26:29,976 --> 00:26:31,394
I'll tell you what.

401
00:26:31,560 --> 00:26:33,896
Ahem. You come on
in here, you...

402
00:26:34,063 --> 00:26:38,567
you sign these papers here,
I'm gonna give you $10 apiece.

403
00:26:38,901 --> 00:26:44,991
Uh, OK, sir, but Mert and...
Aloysious'll have to sign x's.

404
00:26:45,324 --> 00:26:49,328
- Only four of us can write.
- That'd be fine.

405
00:26:52,248 --> 00:26:55,584
Hey, mister, I don't mean
to tell tales out of school,

406
00:26:55,751 --> 00:26:59,588
but there's a fella in there'll pay
you $10 if you sing into his can.

407
00:26:59,922 --> 00:27:02,925
I'm not hear to make a record,
you dumb cracker.

408
00:27:03,175 --> 00:27:05,011
They broadcast me on the radio.

409
00:27:05,261 --> 00:27:08,180
That's Governor Menelaus "Pappy" O'Daniel.

410
00:27:08,514 --> 00:27:12,518
He'd sure like it if you ate his
farina and voted him a second term.

411
00:27:12,852 --> 00:27:15,438
- Finest in Mississippi.
- In any state.

412
00:27:15,771 --> 00:27:17,940
Lord, yes. Every parish.

413
00:27:18,190 --> 00:27:21,027
Ain't you gonna press the flesh, Pappy?

414
00:27:21,193 --> 00:27:24,447
I'll press your flesh,
you dim-witted son'bitch.

415
00:27:24,613 --> 00:27:28,534
Don't tell me how to court the
electorate. We ain't one-at-a-timin'.

416
00:27:28,784 --> 00:27:30,453
We're mass communicatin'!

417
00:27:30,703 --> 00:27:33,289
Oh, yes, that's a powerful new force.

418
00:27:33,539 --> 00:27:34,957
Shake a leg, Junior.

419
00:27:35,207 --> 00:27:37,543
Thank God your mammy died givin' birth,

420
00:27:37,793 --> 00:27:39,378
she'd have died of shame.

421
00:27:39,545 --> 00:27:41,547
Well, hi there! How you doin'?

422
00:27:43,549 --> 00:27:49,138
<i>Hard time yearnin' where you go</i>

423
00:27:49,388 --> 00:27:54,977
<i>Times is harder than ever been before</i>

424
00:28:00,232 --> 00:28:03,319
<i>And the people are driftin'</i>

425
00:28:03,569 --> 00:28:06,072
<i>From door to door</i>

426
00:28:06,322 --> 00:28:07,740
<i>Can't find no heaven</i>

427
00:28:07,907 --> 00:28:11,243
<i>I don't care where they go</i>

428
00:28:21,921 --> 00:28:24,423
<i>Say you had money</i>

429
00:28:24,590 --> 00:28:27,093
<i>You better be sure</i>

430
00:28:27,343 --> 00:28:29,178
<i>These hard times will drive you</i>

431
00:28:29,428 --> 00:28:32,348
<i>From door to door</i>

432
00:28:44,110 --> 00:28:46,529
Let's bed down here for the night.

433
00:28:46,696 --> 00:28:50,366
Yeah, it stinks in that old barn.

434
00:28:50,700 --> 00:28:52,034
Suits me.

435
00:28:52,368 --> 00:28:58,207
Pretty soon it'll be nothin' but
featherbeds and silk sheets.

436
00:29:01,294 --> 00:29:03,045
A million dollars.

437
00:29:03,379 --> 00:29:05,298
Million point two.

438
00:29:05,548 --> 00:29:10,303
- 500,000 each.
- 400, Delmar.

439
00:29:10,469 --> 00:29:17,143
Pete, what are you gonna do
with your share of the treasure?

440
00:29:17,476 --> 00:29:19,979
Go out west somewhere.

441
00:29:20,146 --> 00:29:23,816
Open a fine restaurant.

442
00:29:23,899 --> 00:29:27,403
I'm gonna be the maitre d'.

443
00:29:27,570 --> 00:29:30,323
Greet all the swells.

444
00:29:30,489 --> 00:29:33,826
Go to work every day in a bow tie,

445
00:29:34,076 --> 00:29:36,162
tuxedo.

446
00:29:36,329 --> 00:29:39,915
And all the staff say "yes, sir" and...

447
00:29:40,082 --> 00:29:41,417
"no, sir"...

448
00:29:41,667 --> 00:29:45,087
and "in a jiffy, Pete".

449
00:29:45,421 --> 00:29:49,508
And all my meals for free.

450
00:29:52,428 --> 00:29:54,263
What about you, Delmar,

451
00:29:54,513 --> 00:29:57,683
what are you gonna do
with your share of that dough?

452
00:29:58,017 --> 00:30:01,687
I'm gonna visit them
foreclosin' son of a guns

453
00:30:01,854 --> 00:30:05,524
down at the Indianola Savings and Loan.

454
00:30:05,775 --> 00:30:11,781
Slap that money on the barrel head
and buy back the family farm.

455
00:30:12,031 --> 00:30:16,619
You ain't no kind of man
if you ain't got land.

456
00:30:16,786 --> 00:30:18,704
What about you, Everett?

457
00:30:18,955 --> 00:30:22,708
What you have in mind
when you stole it in the first place?

458
00:30:23,042 --> 00:30:29,298
Ahem. I... didn't have no plan.

459
00:30:29,548 --> 00:30:32,468
Well, that hardly sounds like you.

460
00:30:32,718 --> 00:30:35,972
All right, boys!
It's the authorities!

461
00:30:36,222 --> 00:30:38,808
Your situation is purty nigh hopeless!

462
00:30:38,975 --> 00:30:41,394
Damn, they found our car.

463
00:30:41,644 --> 00:30:44,730
We ain't got the time
and nary the inclination

464
00:30:45,064 --> 00:30:47,483
to chat with you boys any further.

465
00:30:47,733 --> 00:30:49,819
Damn, we got to skedaddle.

466
00:30:50,069 --> 00:30:53,990
I left my pomade in the car.
Maybe I can creep up.

467
00:30:54,323 --> 00:30:58,577
Don't be a fool, Everett.
We got to R-U-N-N-O-F-T.

468
00:30:58,911 --> 00:31:00,830
Where's Tommy?

469
00:31:00,997 --> 00:31:06,252
Already lit out, scared out of his wits.

470
00:31:07,336 --> 00:31:10,256
Let's go!

471
00:31:10,506 --> 00:31:12,508
Well, hell, it ain't square one.

472
00:31:12,675 --> 00:31:16,762
Ain't no one gonna pick up three
filthy, unshaved hitchhikers.

473
00:31:17,096 --> 00:31:21,017
And one of them a know-it-all
who can't keep his trap shut.

474
00:31:21,267 --> 00:31:25,521
The rancour reflected in that remark
I won't dignify with comment.

475
00:31:25,855 --> 00:31:30,026
But I'll address your general
attitude of hopeless negativism.

476
00:31:30,192 --> 00:31:33,029
Consider the lilies of the goddam field.

477
00:31:33,195 --> 00:31:36,282
Or, hell, look at Delmar
as your paradigm of hope.

478
00:31:36,449 --> 00:31:38,117
Yeah. Look at me.

479
00:31:38,367 --> 00:31:42,288
You may call it unreasoning optimism,
