I signed that bill.

958
01:07:59,799 --> 01:08:02,385
I signed a dozen agriculture bills.

959
01:08:02,635 --> 01:08:05,388
Everyone knows I'm a friend of the farmer.

960
01:08:05,721 --> 01:08:08,557
What I gotta do, start diddling livestock?

961
01:08:08,724 --> 01:08:11,978
We can't do that, Daddy.
We might offend our constituency.

962
01:08:12,228 --> 01:08:17,650
We ain't got a constituency!
Stokes got a constituency!

963
01:08:17,733 --> 01:08:19,902
Well, it's a well-run campaign.

964
01:08:20,152 --> 01:08:21,988
Midget and broom and whatnot.

965
01:08:22,238 --> 01:08:25,157
- Devil his due.
- Hell of an organisation.

966
01:08:25,324 --> 01:08:28,577
- Say, I got an idea.
- What's that, Junior?

967
01:08:28,911 --> 01:08:32,415
We can hire us a little fella
even smaller than Stokes's.

968
01:08:32,748 --> 01:08:34,917
You slump-shouldered sack of nuts!

969
01:08:35,167 --> 01:08:38,087
We'd look like a bunch
of johnny-come-latelys

970
01:08:38,254 --> 01:08:40,256
bringin' out our own midget.

971
01:08:40,589 --> 01:08:42,008
Don't matter how stumpy!

972
01:08:42,341 --> 01:08:47,013
That's the goddam problem, people
think Stokes has got fresh ideas.

973
01:08:47,346 --> 01:08:49,432
He's au courant and we're the past!

974
01:08:49,598 --> 01:08:51,017
It's a problem of...

975
01:08:51,267 --> 01:08:52,852
- Perception.
- Right.

976
01:08:53,102 --> 01:08:56,022
- He's pulling our pants down.
- Gonna paddle some behind.

977
01:08:56,188 --> 01:08:58,357
Ain't gonna paddle it. Gonna kick it.

978
01:08:58,691 --> 01:09:02,278
- No, he's gonna paddle it.
- That's not a proper description.

979
01:09:02,528 --> 01:09:09,452
- That's how I'd characterise it.
- It's more of a kickin' situation.

980
01:09:23,215 --> 01:09:28,638
God... God forgive me.

981
01:09:28,971 --> 01:09:33,142
I could not gaze upon that fireshow.

982
01:09:33,392 --> 01:09:36,479
Pete.

983
01:09:36,646 --> 01:09:41,233
- Hold still!
- Can't... stand much longer.

984
01:09:41,484 --> 01:09:44,403
It was... it was
a mo-moment of weakness.

985
01:09:44,654 --> 01:09:46,656
Quit babblin', we gotta skedaddle.

986
01:09:46,906 --> 01:09:48,991
That's all I got.

987
01:09:49,158 --> 01:09:50,826
They lured me out for a bathe

988
01:09:51,077 --> 01:09:54,497
and then they dunked me,
trussed me up like a hog,

989
01:09:54,830 --> 01:09:56,499
and turned me in for the bounty.

990
01:09:56,666 --> 01:09:59,418
Shoulda guessed it.
Typical womanly behaviour.

991
01:09:59,585 --> 01:10:02,088
We're lucky we left before they came back.

992
01:10:02,338 --> 01:10:04,090
We didn't abandon you, Pete.

993
01:10:04,256 --> 01:10:06,509
We just thought you was a toad.

994
01:10:06,676 --> 01:10:09,095
No, they never did turn me into a toad.

995
01:10:09,261 --> 01:10:12,098
Well, that was our mistake, then.

996
01:10:12,348 --> 01:10:17,353
We was beat up by a Bible salesman
and banished from Woolworths.

997
01:10:17,520 --> 01:10:20,523
Everett, was it the one branch
or all of them?

998
01:10:20,773 --> 01:10:23,609
Well, I ain't had it easy, either, boys.

999
01:10:23,776 --> 01:10:28,447
Frankly, uh, well, I...

1000
01:10:29,448 --> 01:10:31,951
I spilt my guts about the treasure.

1001
01:10:35,037 --> 01:10:39,208
I'm awful sorry I betrayed you, fellas.

1002
01:10:39,542 --> 01:10:43,212
Must be my Hogwallop blood.

1003
01:10:44,046 --> 01:10:45,881
That's all right, Pete.

1004
01:10:46,132 --> 01:10:49,135
Awful white of you to take it
like that, Everett.

1005
01:10:49,468 --> 01:10:51,971
I feel wretched.

1006
01:10:52,138 --> 01:10:55,725
Spoiling your play for
a million dollar point two.

1007
01:10:55,975 --> 01:10:58,894
You should rip out my guts.

1008
01:10:59,228 --> 01:11:01,397
No, that's all right.

1009
01:11:03,399 --> 01:11:08,236
You boys are true friends! Ohh!

1010
01:11:08,237 --> 01:11:10,906
You're my beaucoup friends.

1011
01:11:11,115 --> 01:11:15,077
Pete, I don't want you to
beat yourself up about this, eh?

1012
01:11:15,286 --> 01:11:22,293
I can't help it, but
that's a... a wonderful thing to say.

1013
01:11:24,670 --> 01:11:29,300
Yeah. Pete, uh...

1014
01:11:29,884 --> 01:11:34,180
Well, fact of the matter is...

1015
01:11:36,349 --> 01:11:38,017
Damn it...

1016
01:11:38,225 --> 01:11:41,604
There ain't no treasure.

1017
01:11:43,356 --> 01:11:45,608
Fact of the matter is there never was.

1018
01:11:45,983 --> 01:11:47,610
But...

1019
01:11:47,944 --> 01:11:53,783
So where's all the money
from the armoured car job?

1020
01:11:53,866 --> 01:11:56,619
I never knocked over no armoured car.

1021
01:11:56,786 --> 01:12:00,206
I was sent up for
practising law without a license.

1022
01:12:00,456 --> 01:12:02,208
- But...
- I had to bust out.

1023
01:12:02,458 --> 01:12:07,879
My wife wrote me she was
getting married, I gotta stop it.

1024
01:12:07,880 --> 01:12:11,008
I had two weeks left on my sentence.

1025
01:12:11,217 --> 01:12:13,302
I couldn't wait, wedding's tomorrow.

1026
01:12:13,469 --> 01:12:20,476
My added time for the escape,
I don't get out now till 19... 87.

1027
01:12:21,811 --> 01:12:23,562
I am sorry about that.

1028
01:12:23,896 --> 01:12:29,151
I'll be... 84 years old.

1029
01:12:29,402 --> 01:12:33,322
I guess they'll tack on
50 years for me, too.

1030
01:12:33,489 --> 01:12:37,910
Boys, we was chained together.
I had to tell you something.

1031
01:12:38,119 --> 01:12:43,332
Busting out alone
was not an option. I'm sorry.

1032
01:12:43,582 --> 01:12:47,169
84 years old.

1033
01:12:47,253 --> 01:12:50,631
Well, I'll only be 82.

1034
01:12:50,840 --> 01:12:53,592
You! You ruined my life!

1035
01:12:53,926 --> 01:12:56,512
You ruined my life!

1036
01:12:56,887 --> 01:12:58,848
I do apologise, Pete.

1037
01:12:59,181 --> 01:13:03,436
84 years old!
I'm becoming Papillon!

1038
01:13:03,728 --> 01:13:05,229
Delmar!

1039
01:13:09,442 --> 01:13:13,195
Now, boys. Boys.

1040
01:13:26,459 --> 01:13:33,466
<i>Eeny meeny meiny mo</i>

1041
01:14:11,337 --> 01:14:16,717
<i>Oh death</i>

1042
01:14:16,926 --> 01:14:22,014
<i>Whoa death</i>

1043
01:14:22,390 --> 01:14:27,270
<i>Won't you spare me over till another year?</i>

1044
01:14:32,608 --> 01:14:35,486
<i>Well, I am death, none can excel</i>

1045
01:14:35,695 --> 01:14:40,116
<i>I'll open the door to heaven or hell</i>

1046
01:14:40,283 --> 01:14:43,035
<i>Whoa, death, someone would pray</i>

1047
01:14:43,244 --> 01:14:47,999
<i>Could you wait to call me another day?</i>

1048
01:14:48,207 --> 01:14:49,292
<i>Children pray...</i>

1049
01:14:49,542 --> 01:14:54,046
That's Tommy.
They got Tommy!

1050
01:14:55,131 --> 01:14:56,340
Noose.

1051
01:14:56,632 --> 01:14:59,552
<i>No longer prayin'...</i>

1052
01:14:59,927 --> 01:15:04,307
Sweet Jesus, we got to save him.

1053
01:15:04,473 --> 01:15:07,226
<i>I'll fix your feet till you can't walk</i>

1054
01:15:07,393 --> 01:15:12,481
<i>I'll lock your jaw till you can't talk</i>

1055
01:15:12,815 --> 01:15:16,068
<i>I'll close your eyes so you can't see</i>

1056
01:15:16,235 --> 01:15:20,781
<i>- It's very dark...
- The colour guard.</i>

1057
01:15:21,157 --> 01:15:24,744
<i>Death, I come to take the soul</i>

1058
01:15:24,952 --> 01:15:29,498
<i>Leave the body and leave it cold</i>

1059
01:15:29,832 --> 01:15:33,294
<i>Oh death</i>

1060
01:15:33,586 --> 01:15:37,840
<i>Whoa death</i>

1061
01:15:38,049 --> 01:15:43,763
<i>Won't you spare me over till another year?</i>

1062
01:15:45,598 --> 01:15:48,267
Brothers!

1063
01:15:48,601 --> 01:15:51,187
Oh, brothers!

1064
01:15:51,437 --> 01:15:58,444
We have all gathered here to preserve
our hallowed culture and heritage

1065
01:15:59,528 --> 01:16:05,618
from intrusion, inclusion and dilution

1066
01:16:05,785 --> 01:16:08,621
of colour, of creed,

1067
01:16:08,955 --> 01:16:10,873
and of our old-time religion.

1068
01:16:11,123 --> 01:16:15,586
We aim to pull evil up by the root

1069
01:16:15,878 --> 01:16:21,842
before it chokes out the flower
of our culture and heritage.

1070
01:16:22,134 --> 01:16:25,930
And our women,
let's not forget those ladies, y'all,

1071
01:16:26,222 --> 01:16:29,058
looking to us for protection

1072
01:16:29,225 --> 01:16:34,063
from darkies, from Jews, from papists,

1073
01:16:34,355 --> 01:16:37,066
and from all those smart-ass folks

1074
01:16:37,316 --> 01:16:40,069
say we come descended from monkeys.

1075
01:16:40,319 --> 01:16:43,406
- That's not my culture and heritage.
- Yes!

1076
01:16:43,739 --> 01:16:45,074
Is it yours?

1077
01:16:45,408 --> 01:16:47,493
No!

1078
01:16:47,743 --> 01:16:50,329
And so...

1079
01:16:50,496 --> 01:16:52,540
we gonna hang us a Negro.

1080
01:17:06,512 --> 01:17:11,517
I ain't never harmed you,
neither of you gentlemen.

1081
01:17:33,456 --> 01:17:37,376
I ain't never harmed nobody.

1082
01:17:39,128 --> 01:17:41,297
- Hey, Tommy.
- Huh?

1083
01:17:41,589 --> 01:17:43,382
Tommy, we come to rescue you.

1084
01:17:43,633 --> 01:17:45,718
That's mighty kind of you boys,

1085
01:17:45,968 --> 01:17:49,138
but I don't think nothing's
going to save me now.

1086
01:17:49,430 --> 01:17:53,309
The devil's come to collect his due.

1087
01:17:53,601 --> 01:17:55,478
Don't be crazy, Tommy.

1088
01:17:55,686 --> 01:17:57,480
You don't wanna get hanged.

1089
01:17:57,772 --> 01:17:59,857
Well, naw, I don't reckon I do,

1090
01:18:00,066 --> 01:18:04,153
but that's the way it's working out.

1091
01:18:05,571 --> 01:18:07,239
Tommy, I got a plan.

1092
01:18:10,284 --> 01:18:12,828
No!

1093
01:18:17,041 --> 01:18:18,918
The colour guard is coloured.

1094
01:18:21,170 --> 01:18:24,590
Who made them the colour guard?

1095
01:18:26,175 --> 01:18:28,469
Run, boys!

1096
01:18:35,101 --> 01:18:36,185
No, no, son!

1097
01:18:39,188 --> 01:18:43,859
Can't let that flag touch the ground!

1098
01:19:07,633 --> 01:19:09,552
Get your hands off me.

1099
01:19:09,802 --> 01:19:12,263
I can do this myself, get away from me.

1100
01:19:12,555 --> 01:19:14,390
We should hire this man away.

1101
01:19:14,724 --> 01:19:17,018
- Good idea, Pappy.
- Hell of an idea.

1102
01:19:17,226 --> 01:19:20,980
- Can't beat 'em, join 'em.
- He'll join us, run our campaign.

1103
01:19:21,188 --> 01:19:25,276
- Power, wealth...
- No one says no to Pappy O'Daniel.

1104
01:19:25,568 --> 01:19:29,238
- Not with his blandishments.
- And powers of persuasion.

1105
01:19:29,447 --> 01:19:32,575
- What's his name again?
- The campaign manager?

1106
01:19:32,742 --> 01:19:34,577
- Waldrip.
- Vernon Waldrip.

1107
01:19:34,744 --> 01:19:38,331
- Vernon T Waldrip.
- Hmm.

1108
01:19:43,419 --> 01:19:45,630
It's invitation only.

1109
01:19:45,838 --> 01:19:48,758
- We'll have to sneak in.
- Hold on.

1110
01:19:48,924 --> 01:19:50,384
Wait a minute.

1111
01:19:50,593 --> 01:19:52,928
Who elected you leader of this outfit?

1112
01:19:53,095 --> 01:19:57,266
Since we've been following your lead,
we got nothing but trouble.

1113
01:19:57,516 --> 01:20:00,269
I've gotten this close to being strung up

1114
01:20:00,519 --> 01:20:03,522
and consumed in a fire and whipped no end

1115
01:20:03,856 --> 01:20:05,608
and sunstroked and soggied.

1116
01:20:05,858 --> 01:20:07,276
And turned into a frog.

1117
01:20:07,526 --> 01:20:08,976
He wasn't turned into a frog.

1118
01:20:09,153 --> 01:20:13,449
Almost loved up, though.

1119
01:20:13,783 --> 01:20:16,702
So, you're against me now, too?

1120
01:20:16,953 --> 01:20:20,539
Is that how it is, boys?

1121
01:20:21,290 --> 01:20:27,838
The whole world and God Almighty...
now you?

1122
01:20:30,967 --> 01:20:32,718
I guess I deserve it.

1123
01:20:33,052 --> 01:20:36,555
Boys...

1124
01:20:36,889 --> 01:20:39,850
I know that I made some tactical mistakes,

1125
01:20:40,059 --> 01:20:43,145
but if you just stick with me,
I got a plan.

1126
01:20:43,396 --> 01:20:45,731
Believe me, we can fix this thing.

1127
01:20:45,982 --> 01:20:48,484
I'll get my wife back, we'll leave.

1128
01:20:52,571 --> 01:20:55,491
Goddam disgrace!

1129
01:20:55,658 --> 01:20:58,244
Made a travesty of the entire evening.

1130
01:20:58,494 --> 01:21:02,331
Ohh! What I wouldn't give
to get a hold of those agitators.

1131
01:21:02,581 --> 01:21:06,335
Whoever heard of such behaviour,
even amongst the coloured?

1132
01:21:06,585 --> 01:21:11,173
Mulattos, maybe. I suspect some
miscegenation in their heritage.

1133
01:21:11,424 --> 01:21:14,093
Using a Confederate flag as a missile!

1134
01:21:14,427 --> 01:21:17,680
Crazy! No one's ever gonna believe
we're a real band.

1135
01:21:17,888 --> 01:21:20,766
I just gotta get close enough
to talk to her.

1136
01:21:21,017 --> 01:21:24,437
Comin' with us got more future than
marrying a guy called Waldrip.

1137
01:21:24,687 --> 01:21:27,189
I'm goddam bona fide.
I got the answers.

1138
01:21:27,440 --> 01:21:30,693
Everett, my beard itches.

1139
01:21:41,871 --> 01:21:46,459
"In the Jailhouse Now", fellas.
Neighbourhood of B.

1140
01:21:54,550 --> 01:21:58,638
Penny. Ahem.

1141
01:21:59,096 --> 01:22:03,851
- It's me.
- No.

1142
01:22:04,060 --> 01:22:05,353
Honey!

1143
01:22:05,645 --> 01:22:09,315
<i>I had a friend named Ramblin' Bob</i>

1144
01:22:09,523 --> 01:22:12,193
<i>He used to steal, gamble and rob</i>

1145
01:22:12,401 --> 01:22:17,657
<i>He thought he was the smartest guy around</i>

1146
01:22:17,865 --> 01:22:19,158
<i>Well, I...</i>

1147
01:22:19,492 --> 01:22:24,163
We're leaving the state, pursuing
opportunities in another venue.

1148
01:22:24,413 --> 01:22:26,499
I got big plans.

1149
01:22:26,791 --> 01:22:29,502
Not minstrels, I'm going to be a dentist.

1150
01:22:29,752 --> 01:22:34,340
I know this guy
who'll print me up a license.

1151
01:22:34,590 --> 01:22:37,718
<i>He's in the jailhouse now</i>

1152
01:22:37,927 --> 01:22:41,514
<i>Well, I told him once or twice</i>

1153
01:22:41,847 --> 01:22:45,851
<i>To stop playin' cards and a-shootin' dice</i>

1154
01:22:46,060 --> 01:22:49,647
<i>He's in the jailhouse now</i>

1155
01:23:10,209 --> 01:23:12,128
<i>Bob liked to play his poker...</i>

1156
01:23:14,380 --> 01:23:16,549
Why, that is an improper suggestion.

1157
01:23:16,841 --> 01:23:21,887
I can't switch sides
in the middle of a campaign...

1158
01:23:22,054 --> 01:23:25,641
especially to work for a man
who lacks moral fibre.

1159
01:23:25,808 --> 01:23:29,145
Moral fibre?
Why, you pasty-face son'bitch.

1160
01:23:29,353 --> 01:23:30,896
I invented moral fibre.

1161
01:23:31,230 --> 01:23:34,483
Pappy was displaying rectitude
when that egghead you work for

1162
01:23:34,817 --> 01:23:37,111
was still messin' his drawers!

1163
01:23:37,320 --> 01:23:40,072
- Psst! Honey.
- Go away.

1164
01:23:40,281 --> 01:23:42,742
I want to be what
you want me to be, honey.

1165
01:23:42,992 --> 01:23:45,828
I want you and the gals to come with me.

1166
01:23:46,037 --> 01:23:50,833
<i>To stop playin' cards
and a-shootin' dice...</i>

1167
01:23:51,083 --> 01:23:54,503
What are you doing here, Pappy?

1168
01:23:54,670 --> 01:23:56,756
Someone let on we were giving out liquor.

1169
01:23:56,964 --> 01:23:59,925
You'll laugh out the other side
of your face November.

1170
01:24:00,259 --> 01:24:01,927
Pappy'll be laughin' then.

1171
01:24:02,136 --> 01:24:05,848
- Not out the other side of his face.
- Just the regular side.

1172
01:24:19,862 --> 01:24:21,948
They're my daughters, too, Penny.

1173
01:24:22,198 --> 01:24:23,699
Ain't you ever heard of...?

1174
01:24:24,033 --> 01:24:26,285
<i>In constant sorrow</i>

1175
01:24:43,636 --> 01:24:47,473
<i>I am the man</i>

1176
01:24:47,807 --> 01:24:50,393
<i>Of constant sorrow</i>

1177
01:24:50,685 --> 01:24:53,062
<i>I've seen trouble...</i>

1178
01:24:53,271 --> 01:24:55,982
Hot damn!
It's the Soggy Bottom Boys!

1179
01:24:56,357 --> 01:25:00,903
<i>I bid farewell</i>

1180
01:25:01,112 --> 01:25:03,114
<i>To old Kentucky</i>

1181
01:25:03,322 --> 01:25:08,911
<i>The place where I was born and raised</i>

1182
01:25:09,161 --> 01:25:11,664
<i>The place where he</i>

1183
01:25:11,998 --> 01:25:16,210
<i>Was born and raised...</i>

1184
01:25:35,605 --> 01:25:38,065
Holy moly! These boys are a hit!

1185
01:25:38,357 --> 01:25:40,735
But, Pappy, they's integrated.

1186
01:25:40,943 --> 01:25:43,279
Wait a minute.

1187
01:25:43,446 --> 01:25:45,948
Folks don't mind they's integrated.

1188
01:25:46,198 --> 01:25:50,202
You's miscegenated.
All you boys is miscegenated!

1189
01:25:50,578 --> 01:25:51,662
Gimme a microphone!

1190
01:25:52,038 --> 01:25:55,124
Gimme a microphone!
Gimme a microphone!

1191
01:25:55,333 --> 01:26:00,796
These boys is not white.
Hell, they ain't even old-timey.

1192
01:26:01,005 --> 01:26:03,466
I happen to know, ladies and gentlemen,

1193
01:26:03,674 --> 01:26:06,469
that this band of miscreants,
this very evening,

1194
01:26:06,802 --> 01:26:12,224
interfered with a lynch mob
in the performance of its duties.

1195
01:26:12,475 --> 01:26:13,893
It's true!

1196
01:26:14,101 --> 01:26:16,646
See, I belong to a certain secret society.

1197
01:26:16,812 --> 01:26:19,815
I don't believe I gotta
